any through the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This extension\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"the company\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other U.S. world champions expected to compete in Glasgow include 60m hurdles world record holder and defending world indoor championGrant Holloway, reigning Olympic and world outdoor shot put championRyan Crouser, and reigning Olympic and world pole vault championKatie Moon.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9999990927608019, \"rank\": 8.953247441278293e-07, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}, {\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"score\": 0.9999817221625238, \"rank\": 1.7352521216046532e-05, \"text\": \"Holloway\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q40357\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other U.S. world champions\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"hurdles\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2003}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic and world outdoor shot\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"championRyan Crouser\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic and world pole vault\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2182}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA will also be represented by American mile record holderYared Nuguse, American indoor mile record holderElle St. Pierre, 60m American record holderAleia Hobbs, and 2024 U.S. indoor 1500m championCole Hocker, among others.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": [{\"